When executing an Action on a Group like ScaleTo all the children are also effected by the Action. Aka they scale according to the parent group. This does not apply to the Fade\* Actions which modify the Color. the children do not get affected and therefore do not change their alpha.

The following snippet shows the behavior:

=== Snippet ===

public class Test implements ApplicationListener {

```
private Stage stage;

private Image image;

public void create() {
    stage = new Stage(Gdx.graphics.getWidth(), Gdx.graphics.getHeight(), false);

    Group group = new Group("bla");

    group.x = 100;
    group.y = 100;

    image = new Image("img", new Texture(Gdx.files.internal("textures/black_marked_0.png")));

    group.addActor(image);

    ScaleTo scaleTo = ScaleTo.$(3.0f, 3.0f, 3.0f);
    FadeOut fadeOut = FadeOut.$(3.0f);
    Parallel parallel = Parallel.$(scaleTo, fadeOut);

    group.action(parallel);

    stage.addActor(group);
}

public void render() {
    Gdx.gl10.glClearColor(0.5f, 0.5f, 0.5f, 1.0f);
    Gdx.gl10.glClear(GL10.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);

    stage.act(Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime());
    stage.render();
}

public void resume() {
}

public void resize(final int width, final int height) {
}

public void pause() {
}

public void dispose() {
}
```

}

=== Snippet ===

When putting the Parallel Action directly onto the image and not on the group, the image does scale and fade. But putting the action directly on the group does only scale the image.

